msgid "Primary Goals"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/about/writing_style_guide.rst:10
# e02ca65aa044478ab380bbc76e9e1b15
msgid "The main goals for this manual are as follows."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/about/writing_style_guide.rst:13
# b09bd55b95fb4ad8b548ba6f57be2711
msgid "User Focused"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/about/writing_style_guide.rst:13
# 89b724f108384d3685c4684302960635
msgid "While some areas of computer graphics are highly technical, this manual shall be kept understandable by non-technical users."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/about/writing_style_guide.rst:17
# 9ac25e0199924f4fa871d9f9e9bc2222
msgid "Complete"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/about/writing_style_guide.rst:16
# ff1fec9e433748fab804ef3b4cc5a646
msgid "So there is a canonical source of truth for each of Blender's key areas. This doesn't mean we have to document every small detail, but users shouldn't have to rely on searching elsewhere to find the purpose of key features."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/about/writing_style_guide.rst:22
# 19b6371592d24342a3ac379a25a5d406
msgid "Concise"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/about/writing_style_guide.rst:20
# c369214b8a744f479281437de3cb4c6c
msgid "Computer graphics is an incredibly interesting field, there are many rules, exceptions to the rules and interesting details. Expanding into details can add unnecessary content, so keep the text concise and relevant to the topic at hand."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/about/writing_style_guide.rst:29
# 6017e1c93fb743478b275691951c4760
msgid "Maintainable"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/about/writing_style_guide.rst:25
# d0d79de6d68c44ee808cbd6b7d53106f
msgid "Keep in mind that Blender has frequent releases, so try to write content that won.t have to be redone the moment some small change is made. This also helps a small documentor community to maintain the manual."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/about/writing_style_guide.rst:32
# 02e2ce2bff2145a2bcb8dd753884b8e5
msgid "Content Guidelines"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/about/writing_style_guide.rst:34
# 9d4594015ce746b5a57d1f0abfb774d8
msgid "In order to maintain a consistent writing style within the manual, please keep this page in mind and only deviate from it when you have a good reason to do so."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/about/writing_style_guide.rst:37
# 9194c055588040ec9eb8d79c0284e0a8
msgid "Rules of thumb:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/about/writing_style_guide.rst:39
# 22dc010a27544a53a43cee61ae632116
msgid "*Spell checking is strongly recommended.*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/about/writing_style_guide.rst:40
# b4639e7fee154252b78536c60dbf6e53
msgid "Use American English (eg: modeling and not modelling, color and not colour)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/about/writing_style_guide.rst:41
# f44ade0a88654163ba10b99ee923678a
msgid "Take care about grammar, appropriate wording and use simple English."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/about/writing_style_guide.rst:42
# 0c898f04e5f24710b8f2666a5e3dadf5
msgid "Keep Sentences short and clear, resulting in text that is easy to read, objective and to the point."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/about/writing_style_guide.rst:43
# 562cd1e1518b484399f2de545f7935ef
msgid "Including why or how an option might be useful is a good idea."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/about/writing_style_guide.rst:44
# f3367f8431aa4a5bb3c855e36949ff39
msgid "If you are unsure about how a feature works, ask someone else or find out who developed it and ask them."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/about/writing_style_guide.rst:46
# 615d9f7184734120b36a2ec651fef8ad
msgid "To be avoided:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/about/writing_style_guide.rst:48
# fa99ffaa2ec041ac87f36c87e2d103ef
msgid "Avoid to write in first person perspective, about yourself or your own opinions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/about/writing_style_guide.rst:49
# e6e346524ce245b7a5cc335b697db380
msgid "Avoid `weasel words <http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Weasel_word>`__ and being unnecessarily vague, eg:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/about/writing_style_guide.rst:53
# eb284f227e844f969fcad20844979c52
msgid "Avoid including specific details such as:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/about/writing_style_guide.rst:59
# 724221f3ad584d7296ad87162167c8ba
msgid "These details aren't useful for users to memorize and they become quickly out-dated."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/about/writing_style_guide.rst:60
# 47882ed5ee88447da65982f152f5c44a
msgid "Avoid *Product Placement* - unnecessarily promoting software or hardware brands. Keep content vendor-neutral where possible."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/about/writing_style_guide.rst:62
# d9e2d3c9a61647d695cdd44ad89cdf74
msgid "Avoid technical explanations about the mathematical/algorithmic implementation of a feature if there is a simpler way to explain it (e.g. explaining how mesh smoothing algorithms work is unnecessary, but the blending types of a mix node do need a mathematical explanation)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/about/writing_style_guide.rst:65
# 0b3525b022f3446b906c3a851ff4e44e
msgid "Avoid repetition of large portions of text - simply explain it once, and from then on refer to that explanation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/about/writing_style_guide.rst:67
# 0c2c70da90f1455baaaa384114c29897
msgid "In some cases you might also consider defining a ``:term:`` in the **glossary**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/about/writing_style_guide.rst:68
# ccb3b6c738bf4589a6e0437794981f6b
msgid "Avoid enumerating similar options, such as listing every preset or every frame-rate in a drop-down."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/about/writing_style_guide.rst:70
# 331634a533ba47da901d34b0d733d214
msgid "Their contents may be summarized or simply omitted."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/about/writing_style_guide.rst:72
# 84d338c042254815877c481164976706
msgid "*Such lists are only showing what is already obvious in the interface and end up being a lot of text to read & maintain.*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/about/writing_style_guide.rst:74
# abc7c861f5a54a77a48fb23697c89c54
msgid "Avoid documenting changes in Blender between releases, thats what the release notes are for. We only need to document the current state of Blender."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/about/writing_style_guide.rst:76
# 9c54d0d1d98c4869985921990c9937dc
msgid "Unless the unit a value is measured in is obscure and unpredictable, there is no need to mention it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/about/writing_style_guide.rst:77
# 97a45b1dfea54e61ab43bc0ebc79a836
msgid "Do not simply copy the tool-tips from Blender."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/about/writing_style_guide.rst:79
# 60d55685372f470a94abf15e7532deb2
msgid "*People will come to the manual to learn more than is provided by the UI.*"
msgstr ""

